-- Cotton Climbs as Much as 2.2% After Forecast for Higher Prices
-- B y   J a m e s   P o o l e
-- 2012-08-15T01:18:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-15/cotton-climbs-as-much-as-2-2-after-forecast-for-higher-prices.html
Cotton futures advanced as much as
2.2 percent to 73.69 cents a pound after Antonio Esteve,
president of the International Cotton Association, said prices
may gain to 80 cents as  China  builds reserves and Indian
production may decline.  The December contract traded at 72.86 cents at 9:16 a.m.
Singapore time.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
